		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://sypulse.files.wordpress.com/2011/08/imag00541.jpg"></a>This week is color war in Camp David. If you were ever a camper or a counselor, memories should begin to flood]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div><span style="color:#000000;"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-60" title="IMAG0053" src="http://i2.wp.com/sypulse.files.wordpress.com/2011/08/imag00531.jpg?resize=232%2C142" alt="" data-recalc-dims="1" /></span></div>
<div>
<div>
<div><span style="color:#000000;"><a href="http://sypulse.files.wordpress.com/2011/08/imag00541.jpg"><span style="color:#000000;"><img class="size-medium wp-image-61 aligncenter" title="IMAG0054" src="http://i2.wp.com/sypulse.files.wordpress.com/2011/08/imag00541.jpg?resize=233%2C139" alt="" data-recalc-dims="1" /></span></a><span style="color:#000000;">This week is color war in Camp David. If you were ever a camper or a counselor, memories should begin to flood your memory bank when thinki</span><span style="color:#000000;">ng about color war.</span></span></div>
</div>
</div>
<div><span style="color:#000000;"><span id="more-52"></span></span></div>
<div><span style="color:#000000;"> </span>As a camper, I remember being tortured to memorize the song, with the general screaming &#8220;I went all the way down to the other field and couldn&#8217;t hear you guys&#8221;, and &#8221; I went into the other team&#8217;s room and heard them singing and they are so much better than you guys&#8221;. (I guess they didn&#8217;t know about positive reinforcement). We were taught that nothing else mattered in life besides for getting 1st place in marathon. As campers we readily bobbed apples and shaved our legs with Popsicle sticks. We cheered on our teammates during Tug-A-War. At the end of the three days, I remember my heart pounding while waiting for the scores.  And for what? Maybe people remember which team won the following year, but I doubt as the years pass, people still remember. We can say we care because it&#8217;s a huge competition, and competing is always fun. While that is true, I believe the real reason color war is intense is because for three days everyone is working together to achieve a goal. I remember the first thing I did when I used to win color war, was turn to my friend and slap her five. While winning alone is great, winning with a team is a thousand times better.</div>
]]></content:encoded>
